Latest Research Skip Navigation Accessibility enhancement features require Javascript  Site Index  Main Menu Prostate Cancer Treatments and Research - Latest Research Scientists are also looking at ways to stop prostate cancer from returning in men who have already been treated for the disease. These approaches use drugs such as finasteride, flutamide, and LH-RH agonists that manipulate hormone levels.   National Institute on Aging,   U.S. National Library of Medicine National Institutes of Health,   U.S. Department of Health & Human Services Contact us,   Accessibility,   Copyright,   Privacy Last updated: 23 October 2003